# Ways of Working: {{ display_name }}

## Definition of Done

- serializers, permissions, and service logic are covered appropriately
- migrations are reviewed, not just generated
- API behavior is validated end-to-end for changed resources
- auth and permission implications are called out in review
- schema/docs are updated when the contract changes

## Development Workflow

1. design one resource boundary
2. choose the serializer/view/service split deliberately
3. add migrations and persistence changes
4. cover the slice with pytest-django and integration tests

## Review Triggers

Seek architectural review when:

- auth model changes
- serializers start to carry workflow logic
- viewsets become orchestration-heavy
{% if use_celery %}- Celery tasks alter user-visible business flow
{% endif %}
{% if use_channels %}- websocket behavior changes resource consistency expectations
{% endif %}

